#. type: Plain text
#: docs/books/admin_guide/05-vi.md:22
#, no-wrap
msgid "*Visual* (**VI**) is a very popular text editor under Linux, despite its limited ergonomics. It is indeed an editor entirely in text mode: each action is done with a key on the keyboard or dedicated commands.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/books/admin_guide/05-vi.md:24
msgid ""
"Very powerful, it is above all very practical since it is on the whole "
"minimal for basic applications. It is therefore accessible in case of system "
"failure. Its *universality* (it is present on all Linux distributions and "
"under Unix) makes it a *crucial* tool for the administrator."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/books/admin_guide/05-vi.md:26
msgid "Its functionalities are:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '* '
#: docs/books/admin_guide/05-vi.md:30
msgid "Insert, delete, modify text;"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '* '
#: docs/books/admin_guide/05-vi.md:30
msgid "Copy words, lines or blocks of text;"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '* '
#: docs/books/admin_guide/05-vi.md:30
msgid "Search and replace characters."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/books/admin_guide/05-vi.md:32
msgid "## `vi` command"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/books/admin_guide/05-vi.md:34
msgid "The `vi` command opens the *VI* text editor."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/books/admin_guide/05-vi.md:38
msgid "``` vi [-c command] [file] ```"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/books/admin_guide/05-vi.md:44
msgid "``` $ vi /home/rockstar/file ```"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/books/admin_guide/05-vi.md:48
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"| Option       | Information                                       |\n"
"| ------------ | ------------------------------------------------- |\n"
"| `-c command` | Execute VI by specifying a command at the opening |\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/books/admin_guide/05-vi.md:50
msgid ""
"If the file exists at the location mentioned by the path, it is read by VI "
"which is placed in **commands** mode."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/books/admin_guide/05-vi.md:52
msgid ""
"If the file does not exist, VI opens a blank file and an empty page is "
"displayed on the screen. When the file is saved, it will take the name "
"specified with the command."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/books/admin_guide/05-vi.md:54
msgid ""
"If the command `vi` is executed without specifying a file name, VI opens a "
"blank file and an empty page is displayed on the screen. When the file is "
"saved, VI will ask for a file name."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/books/admin_guide/05-vi.md:56
msgid ""
"The `vim` editor takes the interface and functions of VI with many "
"improvements."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/books/admin_guide/05-vi.md:60
msgid "``` vim [-c command] [file] ```"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/books/admin_guide/05-vi.md:62
msgid ""
"Among these improvements, the user has syntax highlighting, which is very "
"useful for editing shell scripts or configuration files."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/books/admin_guide/05-vi.md:64
msgid ""
"During a session, VI uses a buffer file in which it records all the changes "
"made by the user."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/books/admin_guide/05-vi.md:67
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"!!! Note\n"
"    As long as the user has not saved his work, the original file is not modified.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/books/admin_guide/05-vi.md:69
msgid "At startup, VI is in *commands* mode."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/books/admin_guide/05-vi.md:72
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"!!! Tip\n"
"    A line of text is ended by pressing <kbd>ENTER</kbd> but if the screen is not wide enough, VI makes automatic line breaks, _wrap_ configuration by default. These line breaks may not be desired, this is the _nowrap_ configuration.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/books/admin_guide/05-vi.md:74
msgid "To exit VI, from the Commands mode, tap <kbd>:</kbd> then type:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '* '
#: docs/books/admin_guide/05-vi.md:78
msgid "`q` to exit without saving (_quit_);"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '* '
#: docs/books/admin_guide/05-vi.md:78
msgid "`w` to save your work (_write_);"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '* '
#: docs/books/admin_guide/05-vi.md:78
msgid "`wq` (_write quit_) or `x` (_eXit_) to save and exit."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/books/admin_guide/05-vi.md:80
msgid ""
"To force the exit without confirmation, you must add *!* to the previous "
"commands."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/books/admin_guide/05-vi.md:83
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"!!! Warning\n"
"    There is no periodic backup, so you must remember to save your work regularly.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/books/admin_guide/05-vi.md:85
msgid "## Operating mode"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/books/admin_guide/05-vi.md:87
msgid "In VI, there are 3 working modes:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '* '
#: docs/books/admin_guide/05-vi.md:91
msgid "The *command* mode;"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '* '
#: docs/books/admin_guide/05-vi.md:91
msgid "The *insertion* mode;"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '* '
#: docs/books/admin_guide/05-vi.md:91
msgid "The *ex* mode."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/books/admin_guide/05-vi.md:93
msgid ""
"The philosophy of VI is to alternate between the *command* mode and the "
"*insertion* mode."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/books/admin_guide/05-vi.md:95
msgid "The third mode, *ex*, is a footer command mode from an old text editor."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/books/admin_guide/05-vi.md:97
msgid "### The Command Mode"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/books/admin_guide/05-vi.md:99
msgid ""
"This is the default mode when VI starts up. To access it from any of the "
"other modes, simply press the <kbd>ESC</kbd> key."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/books/admin_guide/05-vi.md:101
msgid ""
"All entries are interpreted as commands and the corresponding actions are "
"executed. These are essentially commands for editing text (copy, paste, "
"undo, ...)."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/books/admin_guide/05-vi.md:103
msgid "The commands are not displayed on the screen."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/books/admin_guide/05-vi.md:105
msgid "### The Insert mode"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/books/admin_guide/05-vi.md:107
msgid ""
"This is the text modification mode. To access it from the *command* mode, "
"you have to press special keys that will perform an action in addition to "
"changing the mode."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/books/admin_guide/05-vi.md:109
msgid ""
"The text is not entered directly into the file but into a buffer zone in the "
"memory. The changes are only effective when the file is saved."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/books/admin_guide/05-vi.md:111
msgid "### The Ex mode"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/books/admin_guide/05-vi.md:113
msgid ""
"This is the file modification mode. To access it, you must first switch to "
"*command* mode, then enter the *ex* command frequently starting with the "
"character `:`."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/books/admin_guide/05-vi.md:115
msgid "The command is validated by pressing the <kbd>ENTER</kbd> key."
msgstr ""

