#: docs/books/admin_guide/05-vi.md:349
msgid "## EX commands"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/books/admin_guide/05-vi.md:351
msgid ""
"The *Ex* mode allows you to act on the file (saving, layout, options, ...). "
"It is also in *Ex* mode where search and replace commands are entered. The "
"commands are displayed at the bottom of the page and must be validated with "
"the <kbd>ENTER</kbd> key."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/books/admin_guide/05-vi.md:353
msgid "To switch to *Ex* mode, from *command* mode, type <kbd>:</kbd>."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/books/admin_guide/05-vi.md:355
msgid "### Numbering the lines"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '* '
#: docs/books/admin_guide/05-vi.md:357
msgid "Show/hide numbering:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/books/admin_guide/05-vi.md:359
msgid "`:set nu` and the longer `:set number`"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/books/admin_guide/05-vi.md:361
msgid "`:set nonu` and the longer `:set nonumber`"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/books/admin_guide/05-vi.md:363
msgid "### Search for a string"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '* '
#: docs/books/admin_guide/05-vi.md:365
msgid "Search for a string from the cursor:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/books/admin_guide/05-vi.md:367
msgid "`/string`"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '* '
#: docs/books/admin_guide/05-vi.md:369
msgid "Search for a string before the cursor:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/books/admin_guide/05-vi.md:371
msgid "`?string`"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '* '
#: docs/books/admin_guide/05-vi.md:373
msgid "Go to the next occurrence found:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/books/admin_guide/05-vi.md:375
msgid "<kbd>n</kbd>"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '* '
#: docs/books/admin_guide/05-vi.md:377
msgid "Go to the previous occurrence found:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/books/admin_guide/05-vi.md:379
msgid "<kbd>N</kbd>"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/books/admin_guide/05-vi.md:381
msgid "There are wildcards to facilitate the search in VI."
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '* '
#: docs/books/admin_guide/05-vi.md:383
msgid ""
"`[]` : Searches for a range of characters or a single character whose "
"possible values are specified."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/books/admin_guide/05-vi.md:387
msgid "`/[Ww]ord` : search _word_ and _Word_"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/books/admin_guide/05-vi.md:389
msgid ""
"`/[1-9]word` : search _1word_, _2word_ â¦ _`x`word_ where `x` is a number"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '* '
#: docs/books/admin_guide/05-vi.md:391
msgid "`^` : Search for a string starting the line."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/books/admin_guide/05-vi.md:395
msgid "`/^Word`"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '* '
#: docs/books/admin_guide/05-vi.md:397
msgid "`$` : Search for a string ending the line."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/books/admin_guide/05-vi.md:401
msgid "`/Word$`"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '* '
#: docs/books/admin_guide/05-vi.md:403
msgid "`.` : Search for a word with an unknown letter."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/books/admin_guide/05-vi.md:407
msgid "`/W.rd` : search _Word_, _Ward_ â¦"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '* '
#: docs/books/admin_guide/05-vi.md:409
msgid "`*` : Search for one or more characters, whatever they are."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/books/admin_guide/05-vi.md:413
msgid "`/W*d`"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/books/admin_guide/05-vi.md:415
msgid "### Replace a string"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/books/admin_guide/05-vi.md:417
msgid ""
"From the 1st to the last line of the text, replace the searched string by "
"the specified string:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/books/admin_guide/05-vi.md:419
msgid "`:1,$ s/search/replace`"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/books/admin_guide/05-vi.md:421
#, no-wrap
msgid "**Note:** You can also use `:0,$s/search/replace` to specify starting at the absolute beginning of the file.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/books/admin_guide/05-vi.md:423
msgid ""
"From line `n` to line `m`, replace the searched string with the specified "
"string:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/books/admin_guide/05-vi.md:425
msgid "`:n,m s/search/replace`"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/books/admin_guide/05-vi.md:427
msgid ""
"By default, only the first occurrence found of each line is replaced. To "
"force the replacement of each occurrence, you have to add `/g` at the end of "
"the command:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/books/admin_guide/05-vi.md:429
msgid "`:n,m s/search/replace/g`"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/books/admin_guide/05-vi.md:431
msgid ""
"Browse an entire file to replace the searched string with the specified "
"string:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/books/admin_guide/05-vi.md:433
msgid "`:% s/search/replace`"
msgstr ""

